table-1200-556.caption: Season 1
data: Anthony and Vanessa are concerned that Lindsey's new relationship with Krystof is interfering with the Triad. Kamala and Michael ask their lovers Tahl and Jennifer to move in and they accept.

Distrust of Lindsey leads Anthony and Vanessa to crash a lunch between Vanessa and Krystof to talk about the rules of the triad. The Pod formulates relationship rules but Kamala's outside girlfriend Roxanne leads Michael to question whether that relationship is poly.

Jen's monogamous sister drops by to check out Jen's new digs while Kamala has her hot date with Roxanne and hesitantly inquires about the true level of attraction between Roxanne and Michael. Anthony encourages his wife Lindsey to find a local boyfriend so Lindsey thinks about reconnecting with an ex-lover Jacob, but is he polyamorous?

It's anniversary time for both families! Vanessa plans to propose to Lindsey and Anthony and ask for a life commitment and see what her true place is in the triad. Kamala celebrates 10 years of marriage with Michael with a private date and gives him a very special gift that pushes her own boundaries of possessiveness and jealousy.

The San Diego pod are having a poly potluck as an unofficial housewarming for Jen and Tahl moving in but Jen has issues with some of the people Kamala and Tahl want to invite. Anthony gets an invite to the poly potluck through one of the poly groups he's a member of and convinces Lindsey and Vanessa to check it out, so the Triad heads down to San Diego.

Anthony's parents are selling their childhood home so the Triad takes a trip up north to visit the home one last time and take this opportunity for Lindsey to come out to her mom about being polyamorous. The pod is having a great time on the beach as a family unit which makes Tahl realize how happy he is, and decides he wants to come out to his very conservative parents. Jen disapproves but ultimately, it's Tahls' decision.

In the season finale, San Diego is put to the test when one of Jen's major boundaries is broken - will she and Tahl move out? Meanwhile, the triad contemplates what's next for them and what it means in the eyes of their community and the world.

data: Vincent Libérati, French counterintelligence's best agent, is on a mission in Africa when he finds out that he has a brain tumor. He decides to leave the secret services and live out his final months in Marseille, near his daughter Lola, whom he allowed to grow up for too long without being there, and his ex-wife Alexandra, who is about to start a new life with a brilliant local attorney. Without telling them about his illness, Vincent tries to spend as much time with them as possible, while maintaining contact with his former handlers, who offer him top-secret missions in return for an experimental treatment for his tumor. Vincent's first assignment is to collar a major drug trafficker, who has constantly outwitted the conventional police force. The services put all the resources of a shady new network codenamed Hydra at Vincent's disposal, but he must succeed without arousing the suspicions of his sister Juliette, a young police captain who has recently been posted to the region to solve a murder in which the trafficker is implicated. A complicated investigation lies ahead for our hero, trying to navigate a course between his sister, his ex and his daughter...

As Juliette rapidly closes in on them, the drug traffickers resort to abducting her to stop her investigation. Vincent is on the point of taking down the big boss, but quickly has to change his plans. Not only does he have to catch them in the act for the authorities' benefit, he also has to free his sister from the gangsters' secret hideout. Despite the symptoms of his sickness reappearing at the worst possible moment, Vincent accomplishes his near-impossible mission...

Vincent's next assignment is to infiltrate an arms trafficking network to unmask the mysterious boss, who has escaped all the police's attempts to capture him. At the same time, Juliette is investigating the murder of man who died in a hail of Kalashnikov bullets. Unwittingly, she finds herself impinging on her brother's mission. Vincent decides to make the most of the situation and piggybacks Juliette's investigation until she identifies her target. He also receives significant help from Marie, a provocatively beautiful call girl who works for Hydra and whose regular appearances in our hero's life cannot fail to arouse the jealousy of Alexandra, Vincent's ex...

Juliette zealously moves her investigation forward by arresting intermediaries that Vincent planned to use as pawns in his mission. Even worse, she arrests Marie, which forces Vincent to organize a risky escape operation in his sister's police station. At the same time, Hydra makes a big push to smoke out the boss of the arms trafficking gang by springing a major rival from jail. Vincent once more finds himself torn between the dangers of his mission and the complications provided by the women in his life, especially as Alexandra seems to be having doubts about her upcoming marriage and considering the possibility of starting over with Vincent...

Working undercover on Marseille's docks, Vincent is trying to dismantle a human-trafficking operation that smuggles people into the port in containers. He is nearly unmasked by a dockworker and accidentally kills the man after a frenzied pursuit. Unaware of her brother's involvement, Juliette is assigned to the case of the dockworker's death, while Hydra piles the pressure on Vincent to take down the gang before his identity is revealed. At the same time, his personal life is further complicated by his improving relationship with Alexandra and the discovery that his disease is incurable. Vincent won't allow himself to make false promises to the woman he loves...

table-1200-948.pgTitle: List of Model United Nations conferences
table-1200-948.caption: List of Conferences
data: BrizMUN is the largest city-based MUN conference in Australia, welcoming over 300 local, interstate and international delegates annually. The ninth edition of BrizMUN, scheduled for April 24–27, 2014, is set to be the largest in its history and to continue the conference's history of innovation.

Politics, negotiation and delegation are not confined within the walls of a conference room. At EagleMUNC, neither is the Model UN Experience! EagleMUNC provides a unique opportunity for students to opt for their level of involvement, and pushs the limits of MUN with the unique concept of 40 hours simulation. Employing emergency meetings and encouraging external encounters with fellow participants, EagleMUNC allows high school delegates (9-12) to get a feel for the 360 degrees of politics.

CAIMUN is one of the fastest growing high-school Model UN conferences in Canada. Committed towards providing an accessible Model United Nations experience for delegates from High Schools in Canada and the world, providing financial aid to delegates in need is a priority. CAIMUN has a complete international focus and aims to uphold quality, and creativity and depth/breadth in committees.
Chaitanya Bharathi Institute of Technology Model United Nations

CTMUN is a yearly MUN, organized by CBIT Communicando club. A total of 7 different and varied councils were simulated in the 2011 edition viz. the General Assembly (GA), The Special Political And Decolonization Committee (SPECPOL), The Economic and Social Council (ECOSOC), The Security Council (UNSC) all of which are current bodies of the UN as well as The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), A Futuristic G35 set in 2020 (FG-35) and The League of Nations, a pre-UN world body formed in the aftermath of First Great War (WWI).
[Concordia_International_School_Shanghai_Model_United_Nations|Concordia International School Shanghai Model United Nations]

Columban MUN is a much awaited upcoming Model United Nations Conference which is hosted by St. Columba's School. The school, whose Debating Society is reputed as an excellent debate forum, aims to emulate those very ethos in their inaugural MUN this year. In its first edition, it is simulating 4 conventional committees - UN General Assembly (Fourth Committee), UN Human Rights Council, Organization of American States, and is also introducing the Futuristic NATO committee in the Indian MUN circuit. It is also simulating a conference between the top association football clubs in its committee, the UEFA Champions League.
Delhi College of Arts and Commerce Model United Nations Conference

DMUNC is an annual Model United Nations Conference which is hosted by Delhi College of Arts and Commerce's MUN Society MUNitions. Reputed as one of the pioneers of excellent debate and diplomacy forums, DMUNC has been noted for excellent debate quality, participation and organization. Having reputed Model United Nations participators as part of the society and organizers and various others as participants, DMUNC is one of the most reputed MUNs simulated in India. DMUNC In its second edition it is simulating 3 conventional committees - UN General Assembly, UN Human Rights Council, UN Security Council and an IGO - Organization of Islamic Cooperation.
Dwarkibai Gangadhar Khetan International School Model United Nations
DGMUN is a MUN session held during the Annual Carnvival in 2012. The next is to be held on the 12th of August. It is open to high school as well as university students.
The Espergærde Gymnasium Model United Nations

EGMUN is an annual conference for secondary school students organized and run by students. The EGMUN Conferences are widely known for ambitious political debates and social activities that put students together as both students and as delegates. EGMUN is all about making friendships across borders. EGMUN is the largest MUN conference in Denmark; that pledges us, the Secretariat of the EGMUN, to provide great fun, ambitious debates, and new friendships for all of our participants. Every year in November EGMUN is host to 400 highschool students from Europe, the Middle East and the Americas.

The Five College Model United Nations Conference is a conference for the collegiate Model UN circuit. It is a small crisis based conference, located in the pioneer valley and hosted on campus on one of the members organisations. The clubs involved in the planning and execution of the conference are Mount Holyoke Model UN, Smith Model UN and the UMass International Relations Club. FCMUN is currently in its seventh year.

Held annually in May al Vasile Alecsandri National College, the 1st ranked college in Romania, according to 2011 and 2012 high-school rankings. The conference gathers more than 300 students annually. GalMUN is known for its innovative crisis committee an also for its other committees: SC, MC1 (DISEC), HCHR, SPECPOL, EC, ECOSOC, ECOFIN, ICJ, WHO, COPUOS, GA.

Held at the prestigious university "Georg-August Universitat Goettingen", GoeMUN is organized since 2008. In 2013, the 5th anniversary edition with the main topic "Fight for resources", will be under the patronage of the European Commissioner for Environment, his excellency, Janez Potočnik.
Haberdashers' Aske's Boys' School Model United Nations

Havana Model United Nations, HAVMUN is organized by the UNA Cuba, the University of Havana, the Union of Jurists of Cuba, the Caribbean Human Development Foundation and the Federation of University Students. Is also supported by the UN Sistem in Cuba. HAVMUN is staffed entirely by students of the University of Havana, and is the oldest and largest MUN in Cuba.
Largest annual conference in Germany, held at the University in Hamburg of December. XVth session will reconvene December 5 to 9, 2013, under the topic "Taking Sustainability Seriously".

Indian International Model United Nations was India's Largest Model UN simulation with 1078 delegates in its inaugural session. It follows a new set of rules of procedure which is Asia's only MUNning procedure. IIMUN is run by a group of students from different institutes working together for a common cause.
Istanbul Erkek Lisesi Model United Nations

Istanbul Erkek Lisesi Model United Nations is a conference by IELMUN Club, in Istanbul, Turkey. Even being a High school MUN Conference, is the worlds first and only Model United Nations Conference with three languages English, German and Turkish and also first MUN Conference in German, out of the Germany. Because of being a German foreign high school and its other international relations with tens of universities and high schools, hundreds of university and high school students from countries all over the world participate in IELMUN and experience a high academic level and amazing social activities in the capital of culture and history, Istanbul.
Ivy League Model United Nations Conference
Johns Hopkins University Model United Nations Conference

JHUMUNC is held in Baltimore, Maryland every February. The conference is committed to pushing the edge of history with innovative committees not limited to the present time period or constrained by conventional committee rules. The conference prides itself in providing a small conference atmosphere with the better resources a larger conference. JHUMUNC benefits greatly from strong connections it has with SAIS, one of the best International Relations schools, that is associated with Johns Hopkins University. JHUMUNC also features speakers at the forefront of the fields of international politics and global development. The 16th session of JHUMUNC will be held February 7–10, 2013.

KEMUN II is the second Keele hosted environmental Model United Nations conference in the United Kingdom. With discourse taking place on the environment and development topics, and through support from Keele University, KEMUN is a student-led conference which works closely with influential environmental experts, officials, organisations and bodies. The 2013 conference is scheduled for 15-17 of November 2013.
Kansai High School Model United Nations
Lake Erie International Model United Nations

LEIMUN was originally founded as the Kent State University Ashtabula Campus Model U.N., holding its first high school conference in 1980, and holding collegiate conferences since 1993. Historically, LEIMUN conferences have drawn delegates from high schools in the eastern Great Lakes region, and colleges through the Midwest and Eastern United States. LEIMUN conferences feature small committees, such as Security Councils, to promote delegate opportunities for debate. Beginning in April 2014, the LEIMUN high school conference will be co-sponsored by Youngstown State University and held at YSU's campus.
Leeds MUN will be a new born conference, running its inaugural session from in February 2014.

Leiden Model United Nations (LEMUN) is an annually organised three day Model United Nations (MUN) conference attended by more than 400 high school students each year. The conference is hosted in the stately main building of Stedelijk Gymnasium Leiden (Grammar School of Leiden) and THIMUN affiliated. The conference is known for the relatively small committees of about 40 delegates and the focus on quality over quantity. LEMUN is a very international conference with almost 200 students from abroad, including schools from the United States, Germany, Turkey, Greece, France and Sweden. LEMUN always tries to be innovative with simulations of a Crisis Committeem, the International Criminal Court and an Emergency Special Session during which the Security Council tries to cooperate with the General Assembly in order to find solutions. The first annual session of LEMUN was organised in 2002.
LIMUN is the largest annual university-based Model United Nations conference in Europe. It attracts around 1500 delegates. LIMUN is also registered as a charity in the United Kingdom.

MYMUN, run by Mont' Kiara International School in Malaysia is a THIMUN affiliated conference providing a stimulating MUN experience for middle school students. The conference is open to grades 6, 7 and 8 students from schools where students finish at grade 12. Students in Grade 9 may apply for the Advisory Pane; students Students in Grades 10, 11 and 12 may apply to be Committee Chairs or be part of the MYSPY press team. With more than 300 participants attending from more than twelve schools in Asia, MYMUN is the only middle school conference in Malaysia, and the only middle school conference in the South East Asian sub-continent with THIMUN-affiliation.
Model United Nations of The International School of The Hague

MUNISH is held at The International School of the Hague, in The Hague, Netherlands, at the beginning of November. This is a 3 day conference for students and run by students. The theme of this year's conference is, "Peace and Justice".
Modelo de Naciones Unidas de la Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México.
Modern School International Model United Nations

ModMUN is hosted annually by Modern School in the heart of the capital at Barakhamba Road, Connaught Place. The first session was held in 2011 and was Asia's Largest High School Level Conference. The Model United Nations Society of Modern School has been crowned as one of the best in the nation, winning Best Delegation trophies all over the sub-continent. The Modern School MUN society has won awards at conferences from Harvard MUN, Boston to Aitchison College MUN, Lahore, Pakistan. ModMUN has simulated path-breaking committees like the All India Political Parties Meet, the CIA and Mossad. ModMUN is known for simulating committees that discuss innovative agenda concerning intelligence collection to domestic agendas concerning the political and economic future of a nation of a billion democratic voters.
Modèle Francophone Internationale des Nations Unies en Eurasie

MFINUE is a three-day simulation of the United Nations in French, organized in Lycée Français Saint-Joseph d'Istanbul. With 4 General Assembly committees, 1 ECOSOC, 1 Special Committee, 1 Security Council and 1 International Court of Justice MFINUE invites more than 250 participants. MFINUE is honored to be the largest French MUN of the world.
Model United Nations of the Far West

MUNFW is one of the oldest, continually running Model UN conferences in the United States. Held every April in San Francisco, MUNFW's five-day conference draws more than 500 participants from colleges across the United States, Canada, and further afield.
Model United Nations of the Russian Far East

Model United Nations of the Russian Far East is a non-governmental organization dealing with leadership development and annually organizing International Model UN Conferences and other, both local and international, events. MUNRFE mission: "We build institutions which equip students to: discuss societal problems through open forum debates, launch initiatives, which benefit broader community share knowledge, skills and best practices."
Model United Nations of the University of Chicago

||This international conference, recognized by the United Nations Turkey Office, is organized by Model United Nations Association, Turkey and held annually in March. It is the biggest MUN conference in Turkey with more than 500 delegates. MUNTR, entertaining many students from around the world, has both high quality of debate and social programme.

Attracts more than 1000 student delegates, teachers and parents from around the world at its annual conference which is held at the United Nations. Plus Regional and International Conferences; partnership conferences not limited to Montessori students. exclusively and includes social action projects. Based on a collaboration model as opposed to the standard competition model. Attracts more than 1,000 student delegates, teachers and parents from around the world at its annual conference held at the United Nations Headquarters with UN Ambassadors participating.

NWMUN is the largest Model United Nations conference in the Pacific Northwest, drawing over 350 students to downtown Seattle each November. It is currently held at the Renaissance Seattle Hotel, and is staffed by students from around North America.
OASIS International School Model United Nations

Hosted annually as an international school level conference. The first day is a sports day, the debates are divided on three long days with outings to Cairo's Hotspots every night and a typical visit to Egypt's landmarks on the fifth day. This conference hosts students from countries around the world, ex: Italy, France, Switzerland, Russia, Bangladesh, Saudi Arabia and others...

This conference has a reputation for a high quality of debate. Over 500 students from around the world attend the programme, which is held over a weekend in Oxford, with debate usually taking place in various rooms spread across the University. There is also an active social programme.

This conference is held annually each December in the UNESCO World Headquarters in Paris. It attracts over 900 participants from around the world each year and is known for its very high standards of quality. The conference is organized and run by students from the American School of Paris.
Puebla American School Model United Nations

This conference is held annually each January. It attracts participants from around Mexico and Latin America each year and is known for its high standards of quality. The conference is organized and run by students from the American School of Puebla.

Rotaract MUN vision is to create a system that goes beyond a simple MUN conference, we want for RotaractMUN to become a pillar in international youth decision-making. The conference is designed in such a way that each subsequent edition will take place in a different location on the planet. It will literally jump from one place to another, each year, and discuss the most important international topics, having as agents: youth.

Sponsored by the Institute for Domestic and International Affairs, this conference traditionally hosts 1,000 high school students from around the world, and has been recognized for its emphasis on education. By taking a class at Rutgers University to prepare for their committees and write their topic briefs, RUMUN staff members are some of the most well-prepared committee directors of any conference. The staff's focus on encouraging participation, developing relevant skills, and building conceptual understanding is as evident as their focus on parliamentary procedure and debate moderation. This conference is also unique in that it focuses on a different theme each year.
Santa Rosa International Model United Nations

The second oldest model of United Nations conference in Venezuela and one of the most prestigious in the country, this conference traditionally hosts over 300 delegates from around Venezuela and is characterized for its traditional debate and procedure. its organized by students from the Santa Rosa de Lima School.

Hosted annually by an association of international schools in Korea that is composed of: Yongsan International School of Seoul, Seoul International School, Korean International School, and Seoul Foreign School.

The largest university level conference in Scotland, this conference traditionally hosts over 250 delegates from around the world and is widely renowned for its emphasis on hosting many smaller committees (less than 35 delegates) debating a wide range of topics. The directors are primarily from the Edinburgh University Model United Nations (EDMUN) society.
University of Sheffield Model United Nations
Southeastern High School Model United Nations

SHSMUN is a unique conference in that its officers are high school students themeselves, allowing delegates a rare leadership opportunity. SHSMUN hosts the following committees annually: The Security Council, General Committee, Disarmament and International Security, Economic and Financial, Legal, Social and Humanitarian, Special Political and Decolonization, the UN Environment Programme, the World Health Organization, and an AdHoc Committee. The conference brings over 300 students to downtown Chattanooga each year the weekend before Thanksgiving, typically Saturday through Monday.

The Southern Ontario Model United Nations Assembly is the oldest and largest Model United Nations simulation run entirely by high-schools students in North America. Founded in 1973, the annual conference has run continuously for 40 years. With an international scope and delegates from dozens of nations, the assembly serves to educate participants about current events, topics in international relations, diplomacy and the United Nations agenda. The 41st session of SOMA will be held from April 17–19, 2013, at the University of Toronto's St. George Campus.

SRMUN originated in Greensville, South Carolina in 1990 but moved to its primary location in Atlanta, Georgia in 1991. SRMUN has held over 20 MUN conferences drawing several hundred delegates, normally from the southeastern United States but it has received participation from schools as west as Utah and as north as New York with Pace University. In 2013, SRMUN has branched a new MUN conference in Charlotte, North Carolina planned for April 2013. SRMUN conferences is three days long, typically Thursday to Saturday.
The European International Model United Nations

TEIMUN is the oldest MUN of the European mainland and welcomes more than 240 students from all over the world every year. This year's conference will be held from the 15th to 21 July. The one thing that truly sets TEIMUN apart from other conferences, are the strong social activities throughout the week. This conference has an exciting social program filled with interesting excursions and fabulous parties. TEIMUN 2013 will simulate the following councils: General Assembly, The Security Council, The North Atlantic Council, The International Court of Justice, The Economic and Social Council, The Human Rights Council, the European Council, and the UNESCO Intergovernmental Committee.
The Hague International Model United Nations
The Hague International Model United Nations Singapore
Attracts around 2000 delegates. Held annually at the Hwa Chong Institute in Singapore and is the largest MUN conference in Asia.
[United_Nations_Association_of_the_United_States_of_America|United Nations Association of the United States of America]
United Nations International Student Conference of Amsterdam
United World College of South East Asia Model United Nations

Held in September, it is open to all high schools in South East Asia. The committees being offered at MUN UWCSEA will address a wide array of issues from human rights violations to political controversies, allowing delegates to engage in debates regarding issues they feel passionately about and to meet others that share this passion. The conference’s culturally diverse participants also provide us with the opportunity for students to hone and develop their speaking and negotiation skills, while practicing diplomacy and maintaining international relations.
University College London Model United Nations

The UCLU Model United Nations Society runs an annual conference which is held at the historical campus in central London in January. UCL has a proud and established tradition of being a university that promotes rigorous intellectual debate while embracing cultural diversity. A wide range of notable alumni including Alexander Graham Bell, Mahatma Gandhi, Walter Bagehot and the members of Coldplay attest to this long tradition.
University of California Berkeley Model United Nations
An annual MUN for students held each spring in Uppsala Sweden. The conference is organized by Uppsala Association of International Affairs and Uppsala United Nations association.

Since its inception, VMUN has grown into Western Canada’s premier Model UN experience for high school students, now with approximately 1000 delegates in attendance each conference. The conference offer as wide variety of committees to reflect the diversity and complexity of the modern world, and to provide delegates with the opportunity to discuss, debate, and resolve relevant and contentious issues.
VIT Chennai Model United Nations Conference

It is the first inter-college MUN being organized by the Debate Society of this fledgling campus. Five revolutionary councils namely, Historic General Assembly, NATO-OIC, UN Security Council, UN Environment Programme and The Council of the European Union. VITCMUN will take place from 22–24 March 2013. The conference will be hosting participants from all over India.

Central India's Largest Conference attracts maximum number of international participants amongst all MUNs in India. All the agendas were based on economics as the theme was "Economics for change". VMUN is famous for it's prize money and the quality of debate.
Washington Area Model United Nations Conference

WAMUNC, the annual high school conference hosted by the George Washington International Affairs Society (GWIAS) attracts close to 1,000 delegates each spring. In addition to the typical GA, ECOSOC, regional and historical committees, WAMUNC is one of the few conferences that regularly features joint crisis committees with three or more committees.
William & Mary High School Model United Nations Conference

WMHSMUN is the annual high school Model United Nations conference held by the William & Mary International Relations Club (WMIRC) and brings between 1,000 and 1,500 delegates to the William & Mary campus every fall. The conference regularly features novice committies, general assemblies, specialized agencies, joint crisis committies, and its most prestigious committee, the Ad-Hoc Committee of the Secretary General, which is available by application.
Modelo Internacional de Naciones Unidas Buenos Aires

MINUBA takes place every October in Buenos Aires, Argentina organised by Asociación MINU. It simulates 5 commissions or committees in Spanish (usually General Assambly, Security Council, ECOSOC, UNHCR, HRC) and one in English. It is one of the biggest and most important MUN in Latin America and participants(mainly from Buenos Aires Metropolitan Area) come from all over the continent and Spain. Asociación MINU also helds simulations of the Argentine Congress.

Youth Model United Nations was the first ModelUN conference in the Indian city of Haryana. The conference, held on the campus of the Lingaya's University, hosted over 200 delegates. University students also participated as delegates and secretariat. YouthMUN was the first to host United Nation's Global compact alongside UNGA, UNSC and the ECOSOC.

Hosted annually as one of India's most diverse Model United Nations Conference at Mahindra United World College's beautiful campus. UWCCI is organized in collaboration with the UN Information Centre for India and Bhutan. The 2013 Conference features Secretary Generals Naman Shah and Shaibyaa Rajbhandari along with a highly skilled core team, headed by faculty advisor Zia Pochkhanawala.
Beijing National Day School Model United Nations
Beijing National Day School Model United Nations was created in 2005 by about 10 students.
University of Salerno Model United Nations
Hosted annually as an international university level conference. Located on the Amalfi Coast is the only MUN in Southern Italy.

data: Chris makes an effort to spend more time Leigh Ann but her outside commitments continue to interfere. Michael worries that Kamala's new boyfriend is drawing too much of her focus.

Things have been strained with the trio with Leigh Ann traveling for work. Chris and Megan pick up Leigh Ann from the airport only to discover what's really been going on in Leigh Ann's world. Kamala asks Michael to go deeper with his new girlfriend Rachel so he can try to develop more of an emotional relationship than a sexual relationship.

Leigh Ann gets kicked out of the house while Megan decides if she wants to be in a relationship with Leigh Ann. Tahl breaks a rule on his date with his girlfriend and Michael, Rachel and Kamala's threesome has an unexpected outcome.
Michael's jealousy issues come to a head when Jason and Kamala break one of his rules, and Leigh Ann faces an ultimatum.

Tensions run high in Hollywood when Chris and Megan come face to face with Leigh Ann and her boyfriend. In San Diego, Tahl and Christian prepare for their date and Jen is in for a surprise on her weekly date with Kamala.
Chris and Leigh Ann are apprehensive on their date, and Tahl and Christian consider taking the next step in their relationship.
The San Diego pod heads prepare for their annual lover's getaway and Chris, Leigh Ann, and Megan finally come face-to-face to discuss the future of their relationship.

table-1200-156.caption: December 18 event
data: Tornado injured one person as it unroofed three homes and removed one of them from its foundation. It is officially rated F1 but one authority accepts an F2 ranking (Grazulis 1991).

Tornado was initially assumed to have occurred at the same time as the McBride tornado but this assessment was changed. It is officially ranked F2 but may have been weaker and is thus not treated as significant by Grazulis (1991).

Tornado damaged or destroyed buildings on 10 farm sites. Damage path skipped and was not continuous. Was the first of two tornadoes to hit near Chester, this one hitting north of the town. The next event hit southeast of Chester.
Tornado damaged or destroyed nine buildings in south Wood River. One authority unofficially ranks the tornado at F3 intensity (Grazulis 1991).
Tornado caused minimal damage to three or four buildings. One person was injured.
Tornado injured two people while unroofing or severely damaging eight buildings.
Tornado damaged three or four homes. It is not listed as an F2 event by Grazulis (1991).
Second tornado to hit Mt. Vernon struck the north side of town, hitting and damaging 12 buildings, including six farms and six homes. Tornado is unofficially rated F3 by Grazulis (1991).

Tornado injured one person and destroyed buildings on 20 different farm sites. The most intense damage occurred as the tornado touched down, then became less severe and discontinuous. It dissipated just south of downtown Clay City. Another, unconfirmed tornado may have hit the same area at 2330 UTC.
Tornado destroyed homes in parts of Dahlgren and caused F3 damage along its very short path. It may have been produced by the same thunderstorm that spawned the F5 Sunfield tornado.
Tornado injured four people as it destroyed four or more barns and a home along its path.
Tornado was apparently heard to produce a "'roaring'" noise with minimal damage.
Sources: Tornado Data for December 18, 1957, Grazulis 1991

Damaged The Naval Historical Center listing states that USS Barry (APD-29) was "damaged by Kamikaze attack off Okinawa, Ryukyu Islands, 25 May 1945, and sunk as a decoy, 21 June 1945." This description does not make clear how Barry sank on June 21, 1945. The Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships describes the sinking as follows: Barry was towed to the anchorage at Kerama Retto 28 May and found too extensively damaged to warrant repair or salvage. Stripped of useful gear, she was decommissioned 21 June 1945. Later in the day she was towed from the harbor of Kerama Retto to be used as a decoy for the kamikazes. While under tow she was attacked by Japanese suicide planes and sunk along with her escort, LSM-59. There is another account of the sinking: Kimball (2007), a crew member of fleet tug USS Lipan (ATF-85), tells the story of the sinking of Barry by a kamikaze plane: The USS Barry was an old four-stacker Destroyer commissioned around 1920 and modernized and converted into a high-speed troop transport and reclassified as an APD. It took some hits and was intentionally run up on the beach to avoid sinking in deep water and it spent sometime just sitting there. The High Command was experimenting with methods of defending against the relentless kamikaze attacks by the Japanese pilots and it was decided to use the Barry as a decoy to attract the suicide pilots. Since Barry was stripped of all usable equipment its hulk was expendable. Lipan's divers put a soft patch on the hull of the Barry and its interior was filled with empty sealed 5" ammo containers. It was hoped the sealed containers would act as flotation gear and make the Barry less vulnerable to sinking from direct hits. The Barry was fitted with remote controlled flashing lights that looked like anti-aircraft gun muzzle flashes from the air. It also had smudge pots placed at strategic locations and remotely controlled to simulate stack smoke and damage from attacks. From the air it looked like a fully operational Destroyer and it was intended to draw the kamikaze pilots to it and away from the nearby manned vessels. The LSM contained the remote controls for the Barry's pseudo weapons and Lipan was to tow the Barry to simulate an underway tin can. It didn't take long before two kamikaze planes appeared just ten feet off the water equipped with huge bombs strapped to their belly to create a gigantic explosion when they slammed into a vessel. To our dismay, the first attacking Japanese plane slammed into the small USS LSM-59 and hit it directly amidships. The resultant explosion blew the ship into the hereafter and there was not one recognizable part left floating and at least sixty sailors met their demise. We hadn't anytime to think as the second kamikaze climbed straight up to make a dive on us and the Barry. I was a gunner on the 40mm and we gave him all we had, shooting off his wings and setting him afire. Nevertheless, he was able to slam into the Barry and hit her right on the bridge. We could not save her so we tried to tow her to Ie Shima. In the middle of the night the Barry started to sink and was pulling our old "Green Dragon" down by the stern. We had a pelican hook rigged and a sailor hit the release and the Barry slipped from our grasp and headed for Davy Jones' Locker.
